.TH "__tty_alloc_driver" 9 "__tty_alloc_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__tty_alloc_driver \- - allocate tty driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tty_driver *" __tty_alloc_driver
.BI "(unsigned int lines "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ","
.BI "unsigned long flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lines" 12
count of lines this driver can handle at most
.IP "owner" 12
module which is responsible for this driver
.IP "flags" 12
some of TTY_DRIVER_* flags, will be set in driver->flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should not be called directly, some of the provided macros should be
used instead. Use IS_ERR and friends on \fIretval\fP.
